.TH "ntfs_remount" 9 "ntfs_remount" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntfs_remount \- change the mount options of a mounted ntfs filesystem
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ntfs_remount
.BI "(struct super_block *sb "  ","
.BI "int *flags "  ","
.BI "char *opt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sb" 12
superblock of mounted ntfs filesystem
.IP "flags" 12
remount flags
.IP "opt" 12
remount options string
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Change the mount options of an already mounted ntfs filesystem.
.SH "NOTE"
The VFS sets the \fIsb->s_flags\fP remount flags to \fIflags\fP after
\fBntfs_remount\fP returns successfully (i.e. returns 0).  Otherwise,
\fIsb->s_flags\fP are not changed.
